servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/al-pastor-pork-60ae4c4ce4497024a537485b
---

Wash and dry all produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine 1 cup water (2 cups for 4 servings), @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then add @White Quinoa{1/2%cup}; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until quinoa is tender and liquid has absorbed, ~{15-20%minutes}. TIP: Drain any excess liquid if necessary.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While quinoa cooks, drain @Pineapple{4%ounce} over a #small bowl{}, reserving juice; roughly chop fruit. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}(zested and quartered). Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(thinly sliced). Finely chop @Cilantro{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped).

To #bowl{} with pineapple juice, stir in @Tex-Mex Paste{1}, 2 TBSP water (3 TBSP for 4 servings), and juice from half the lime.

== Pineapple Salsa ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine chopped pineapple, scallions, half the cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Pork ==

Pat @Pork Chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with half the @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. TIP: If pork begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Return same pan to medium-high heat. Add pineapple juice mixture and bring to a simmer. Cook until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) until melted.

== To Serve ==

Fluff quinoa with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and remaining cilantro. Season with salt and pepper. TIP: For extra-rich quinoa, stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Thinly slice pork crosswise.

Divide quinoa between bowls and top with pork. Drizzle pork with pan sauce, then top with pineapple salsa and @Smoky Red Pepper Crema{2%tablespoon}. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.